Class HabitationEntity

java.lang.Object
  at.fhv.roomanizer.persistence.entity.service.ServiceEntity
      at.fhv.roomanizer.persistence.entity.HabitationEntity

public class HabitationEntity
extends ServiceEntity

Represents a habitation in the hotel. In our system a habitation only contains one room, which means for bigger groups of people, living in different rooms, the system manages multiple habitations. Additionally to the standard information the habitation contains informationabout the room, the guest who lives in the room during the habitation, the employee which did the checkin, and the invoiceItems, which have to be payed at the checkout.

Author:
Daniel Rotter
